9:
The new year has just begun, and
already you are hard at work.
13:
Good morning. I must start the new
year correctly.
15:
They say excellence isn't any one
act, but a habit. And I don't intend
on taking a single day off.
18:
Well, if not a full day, how about a
few hours? Alk should be done
making breakfast by now. Come
and join us.
21:
Of course. It would be an honor to
eat at your table!
24: It is a strange feeling being idolized...
28:
This is excellent! Alk, you have
outdone yourself yet again.
35:
Naw... I just learned how to use soy
sauce and local seasonings, that's
all.
40: What's wrong? Don't like the food?
45:
I find it odd Alk would put so much
effort into his cooking.
48:
Back home, we believe it's the job of
the strong to fight. Household affairs
are left to, well, everyone else.
51:
Oh. Sounds like the Farlands need to
get with the times.
58:
Heh. When Yuwel talks, all I hear is a
spoiled rich kid. You have servants
bathe and dress you too?
71:
My point is, warriors needn't know
how to cook.
75:
Is that so? When I was human, I
would sometimes make simple
mealsâ€”
80:
OR RATHER, warriors of OLD needn't
have known how to cook. Of course
all great warriors NOW wield pans
just as well as they wield swords!
83:
I am the last of the Swallow Knights.
It is my duty to be master of both
field and scullery!
97:
He had. A whole outfit.
Custom-made.
100:
If a silver spoon falls out of his
mouth, and no one's around to hear
it, do you think he's still rich?
108:
Now, I'm to make traditional Yamato
stew, am I? Well, I've gathered only
the best ingredients, so my "zoni"
will be flawless!
110:
If you would please wait here, I will
have the food ready in a moment.
114: I've got a bad feeling about this...
121: I think I'd better go check on him...
127:
CHOCOLATE?! Why would you use
CHOCOLATE?!
131: Because you LIKE IT?! THAT'S NOTâ€”
134:
NO! Fish sauce and soy sauce are
two completely different things!
Yuwel... PUT THE SURSTROMMING
DOWN!
139: Go away! I know what I'm doing!
143:
STOP! You can't fix it! Unless you'd
like to suck out all the CHOCOLATE
you dumped in!
147: All we can do... is trust to fate...
152: Not for all the gold in the world.
159:
Sir Light... You wouldn't turn your
back on me, would you?
163: Is this... a test of my courage?
172: You are... even worse... than me...
192:
How are you feeling? I hope you
aren't too... upset.
198:
It is nothing to apologize for. We all
have our strengths and weaknesses.
Perhaps you were simply not meant
toâ€”
202: No! I haven't given up yet.
205:
Alk will not get the better of me. I
WILL make zoni! My pride
depends on it.
208:
I... I'll make sure to taste the food
myself so you needn't worry...
211:
I understand.
May good fortune preserve you.
